fix: up-portainer.sh auto-detects stale portainer.conf and re-renders

A previous bootstrap may have rendered an outdated portainer.conf template
(the one that combined `include proxy-common.conf` with `proxy_read_timeout
3600s` in the same location). nginx rejects that combination as a duplicate
directive. The idempotent render-skip in up-portainer.sh would then leave
the bad file untouched on rerun.

up-portainer.sh now detects the specific bad pattern (presence of both
`include /etc/nginx/snippets/proxy-common.conf` and `proxy_read_timeout` in
the rendered file) and forces a re-render in that case.

Recovery for affected hosts:

    git pull
    ./scripts/up-portainer.sh

The --force flag still exists for manual overrides but the auto-detect
covers the upgrade path automatically.
